                me \Jac(X)(L) = \Pic^0(X\otimes L)
        remark
            p
                | This is false as stated unless #[m X(k) \ne \emptyset].


        proof
            p
                | Idea:
                | Pick #[m P_0 \in X(k)] we have a bijection
                me \divisors^0(X) \to \divisors^r(X)
                me D \mapsto D + r[P_0]
